# CEO review

## Persona: trader
_End-user trader running the EA on a live or demo account._

- [ ] **trader-01** (critical) — What is the maximum acceptable drawdown for this strategy?
- [ ] **trader-02** (critical) — What instruments and timeframes is this EA approved to trade?
- [ ] **trader-03** (critical) — What is the per-trade risk percentage and how is it enforced?
- [ ] **trader-04** (critical) — Is there a daily-loss kill switch and when does it fire?
- [ ] **trader-05** (critical) — Does the EA respect news windows / session boundaries?
- [ ] **trader-06** (high) — How will I know the EA is functioning (journal cues, dashboard, alerts)?
- [ ] **trader-07** (high) — What happens to open positions if the EA is detached or restarts?
- [ ] **trader-08** (high) — Is there a manual override and how do I trigger it safely?
- [ ] **trader-09** (high) — What is the expected number of trades per day / week?
- [ ] **trader-10** (high) — What spread / commission environment is the strategy tuned for?
- [ ] **trader-11** (high) — How is leverage selected and constrained?
- [ ] **trader-12** (high) — Does the EA handle weekend gap risk explicitly?
- [ ] **trader-13** (standard) — What evidence supports the claimed expectancy (sample size, time span)?
- [ ] **trader-14** (standard) — How are losing streaks bounded behaviourally (rule, not feeling)?
- [ ] **trader-15** (standard) — What is the worst historical drawdown sequence and recovery time?
- [ ] **trader-16** (standard) — Are trade reasons logged in a human-readable form?
- [ ] **trader-17** (standard) — What is the rollback procedure if a release misbehaves?
- [ ] **trader-18** (standard) — How is performance reported back to me (daily, weekly, ad-hoc)?
- [ ] **trader-19** (standard) — What's the policy if a broker changes execution rules mid-run?
- [ ] **trader-20** (standard) — Are my expectations on uptime aligned with the chosen hosting?
- [ ] **trader-21** (standard) — How is success/failure of a trade communicated post-mortem?
- [ ] **trader-22** (standard) — What position sizing rule applies for compounding vs fixed?
- [ ] **trader-23** (standard) — Are entry/exit signals deterministic given identical input bars?
- [ ] **trader-24** (standard) — Have I personally validated the EA on demo for at least 2 weeks?
- [ ] **trader-25** (standard) — Do I understand all configurable inputs and their failure modes?

## Persona: strategy-architect
_Quant or strategy author owning signal & expectancy design._

- [ ] **strat-01** (critical) — Is the trading hypothesis stated in one sentence and falsifiable?
- [ ] **strat-02** (critical) — Is sample size (trades) sufficient for the chosen expectancy claim?
- [ ] **strat-03** (critical) — Does walk-forward IS/OOS correlation stay above 0.5?
- [ ] **strat-04** (critical) — Does Monte-Carlo 95th-percentile DD respect the 1.5× tolerance?
- [ ] **strat-05** (critical) — Is OOS/IS Sharpe ratio above the overfit threshold (≥ 0.7)?
- [ ] **strat-06** (high) — Are entry and exit rules deterministic from inputs alone?
- [ ] **strat-07** (high) — Has parameter sensitivity been characterised (cliff vs plateau)?
- [ ] **strat-08** (high) — Is the optimization budget (passes) and selection rule documented?
- [ ] **strat-09** (high) — Is data snooping bias controlled (held-out OOS window untouched)?
- [ ] **strat-10** (high) — Is the regime (trend/range/news) the strategy targets explicit?
- [ ] **strat-11** (high) — Does the strategy degrade gracefully outside its target regime?
- [ ] **strat-12** (high) — Is the chosen fitness metric appropriate (Sharpe vs profit-DD)?
- [ ] **strat-13** (standard) — Has feature-engineering / lookback been peer-reviewed?
- [ ] **strat-14** (standard) — Is there a documented edge thesis (why this works, why now)?
- [ ] **strat-15** (standard) — Are dependencies on broker-specific quirks minimised?
- [ ] **strat-16** (standard) — Does the EA distinguish profit from luck via robustness metrics?
- [ ] **strat-17** (standard) — Have correlated-signal redundancies been reduced?
- [ ] **strat-18** (standard) — Is the cost model (spread + commission + swap) realistic?
- [ ] **strat-19** (standard) — Does live-canary plan compare to backtest within tolerance?
- [ ] **strat-20** (standard) — Is the rolling-window re-optimisation cadence documented?
- [ ] **strat-21** (standard) — Are exits (take-profit vs trail vs time-stop) jointly evaluated?
- [ ] **strat-22** (standard) — Have failure-mode strategies (kill-switch) been signal-tested?
- [ ] **strat-23** (standard) — Is the published expectancy net of all known costs?
- [ ] **strat-24** (standard) — Has fitness vs out-of-sample been visualised for selection bias?
- [ ] **strat-25** (standard) — Are scientific notes (assumptions, observations) checked-in?

## Step templates

### vision

# Step 3 / 8 — VISION (Contractor proposal)

Translate the RRI matrix into a scope + cost + timeline + risk register.

## Inputs
- `step-2-rri.md`

## Activities
- [ ] Define the minimum viable change set (files in, files out)
- [ ] Estimate effort by file (S/M/L)
- [ ] Enumerate risks; assign owner + mitigation

## Outputs
- `step-3-vision.md` — scope, timeline, risk register

## Exit criteria
- Scope is acceptable to all RRI personas active in the chosen mode
- Risks above the personal-mode acceptance bar have explicit mitigations

> Sentinel: `touch .rri-state/vision.done`.


### refine

# Step 8 / 8 — REFINE

Classify the delivered change against the v5 refine envelope and decide
whether to ship, loop back to RRI, or escalate.

## Inputs
- `step-7-verify.md`
- Live canary observation (if applicable)

## Activities
- [ ] Diff scope vs `step-3-vision.md` — are we still inside the envelope?
- [ ] Capture any new pain points → seeds for next SCAN
- [ ] If a gate failed: decide repair vs roll-back; document why

## Outputs
- `step-8-refine.md` — verdict (SHIP / LOOP-TO-RRI / ESCALATE), follow-up items

## Exit criteria
- Verdict recorded
- If SHIP: `mql5-deploy-vps` invoked + MIGRATE-VPS.md produced
- If LOOP-TO-RRI: open a new ticket pointing back to step 2

> Sentinel: `touch .rri-state/refine.done`.

